						               													<description>Contents:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;One spinner, one queen sized sheet.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the back of the box:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;For best results more than one player is needed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The object of Bedlam is to maneuver you and your partner into the most compromising positions possible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To start, each player sits on the Bedlam sheet. Sensuous bedroom attire and a bottle of wine can add pleasure to the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player takes turns spinning the Bedlam spinner. When the spinner points to one of the four colors the player who spun may move a hand or foot to that color. Knees and elbows may touch the sheet.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If the spinner points to Anything Goes, that player is given complete freedom of movement over the entire Bedlam sheet. This player may position their body any place on the game sheet as long as the other player(s) do not move from their positions. When the player is satisfied with their position, play resumes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a player spins Your Request, the player who spun may position the other players on the Bedlam sheet in any position desired as long as they do not move from their position.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When the players have reached compromising positions, Bedlam is declared and you take it from there. Have fun and remember, 'It's not whether you win or lose but Where you play the game'.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Re-implements:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Twister&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
